This paper is about pre-trained models for natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper discusses various machine learning techniques used in pre-training models, such as deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) in some PTMs. However, since the focus of the paper is on NLP, we can rule out cs.CV as a less likely category. Overall, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
